de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating.impl
Class IntegerIncrementGenerator

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating.impl.IntegerIncrementGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Generator, GenericGenerator
public class IntegerIncrementGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Generator

This Generator provides a sequence of IntConstant objects at which each value is succeeded by one that is increased respectively decreased by a specified value (1.0 by default). The starting value and the increment are customizable.

Examples sequences:

  • 0, 1, 2, 3,..., Integer.MAX_VALUE
  • 0, -1, -2, -3,..., Integer.MIN_VALUE
  • 5, 6, 7, 8,..., Integer.MAX_VALUE

Constructor Detail

IntegerIncrementGenerator

public IntegerIncrementGenerator()
Construct the Generator with standard settings. The first Integer will have a value of 0 and each successor will be increased by 1. The maximum value is Integer.MAX_VALUE.

IntegerIncrementGenerator

public IntegerIncrementGenerator(int increment)
Construct the Generator with customized settings for the increment. The starting value is 0 and successors always have a increased value. The maximum value is Integer.MAX_VALUE.

Parameters:
increment - The increment. By this value each integer will be greater/less than its successor.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the increment is zero or less than zero.

IntegerIncrementGenerator

public IntegerIncrementGenerator(int startAt,
                                 boolean countDown)
Construct the Generator with customized settings for the starting value and the direction. The increment is 1. The maximum value is Integer.MAX_VALUE.

Parameters:
startAt - The first Integer returned by the generator.
countDown - If set to true, the value will be decreased with each Integer provided.
